{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "Recent research has also increasingly shown that LLMs can be instrumental in developing AI agents (Palo et al., 2023; Wang et al., 2023a; Xi et al., 2023; Shen et al., 2023; Patil et al., 2023; Qin et al., 2023).",
    "Examples such as ToolFormer (Schick et al., 2023), Auto-GPT (AutoGPT, 2023), BabyAGI (BabyAGI, 2023), KwaiAgents (Pan et al., 2023) and ToolCoder (Zhang et al., 2023a) demonstrate LLMs' proficiency in tool utilization for complex tasks.",
    "Some studies such as self-edit (Zhang et al., 2023b) and self-debug (Chen et al., 2023) have demonstrated that code models possess the capability for multi-round interaction and repair.",
    "Nowadays, some work has also demonstrated the effectiveness of agent systems in complex code programming tasks, such as OpenDevin (OpenDevin, 2024), SWE-Agent (Yang et al., 2024).",
    "In this paper, we select GPT-4 (GPT-4, 2023), GPT-3.5 (GPT-3.5, 2023), and other powerful LLMs to design coding agent systems for real-world repo-level code generation."
  ],
